WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:04.086
{\an7}Ned: IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL
FULL OF BULLIES...

00:04.170 --> 00:06.089
{\an8}INSANE TEACHERS...

00:06.172 --> 00:08.842
{\an8}AND GROSS SCHOOL LUNCHES...

00:08.925 --> 00:11.094
{\an8}NED BIGBY, THAT'S ME,
AND MY 2 BEST FRIENDS

00:11.177 --> 00:12.595
{\an8}TRY TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE:

00:12.679 --> 00:15.598
{\an8}CREATE A GUIDE THAT WILL
HELP YOU SURVIVE SCHOOL.

00:15.682 --> 00:18.977
{\an8}♪ COMING UP, LOOKING OUT ♪

00:19.060 --> 00:21.938
{\an8}♪ I'LL SURVIVE IT, NO DOUBT ♪

00:22.021 --> 00:25.275
{\an8}♪ NEVER FEAR, BRING IT ON ♪

00:25.358 --> 00:27.610
{\an7}♪ BREAKING DOWN
WHAT'S IN MY WAY ♪

00:27.694 --> 00:32.115
{\an8}♪ AND I'M TAKING CONTROL ♪

00:32.198 --> 00:34.784
{\an7}♪ AND FEELING MY PLACE
IN THIS WORLD ♪

00:34.868 --> 00:37.120
{\an8}♪ AND I... ♪

00:37.203 --> 00:38.955
{\an8}Ned: "NED'S DECLASSIFIED
SCHOOL SURVIVAL GUIDE."

00:39.038 --> 00:40.039
{\an8}YOUR RESULTS MAY VARY.

00:41.875 --> 00:44.043
YES! I'M FIRST IN LINE
FOR THE BUS.

00:44.127 --> 00:46.296
{\an1}I WANT TO GET A GOOD SEAT
SO FAYMEN WILL SIT WITH ME.

00:46.379 --> 00:48.590
WHAT'S SO GREAT ABOUT
FAYMEN PHORCHIN?

00:48.673 --> 00:50.508
{\an1}HE'S LIKE
AN UNDISCOVERED GEM.

00:50.592 --> 00:51.426
{\an1}AND IF HE SITS BY ME
ON THE BUS,

00:51.509 --> 00:53.720
I'LL KNOW HE LIKES ME.
IT'S LIKE A LOVE TEST.

00:53.803 --> 00:55.472
SPEAKING OF LOVE TESTS,

00:55.555 --> 00:57.432
{\an5}YESTERDAY
I TUCKED A SURPRISE
EMOTIONAL NOTE

00:57.515 --> 00:58.933
IN SUZIE'S LOCKER.

00:59.017 --> 01:00.769
YOU GUYS HAVEN'T BEEN
GOING OUT THAT LONG.

01:00.852 --> 01:02.145
{\an1}IT'S KIND OF EARLY
TO BE GETTING EMOTIONAL.

01:02.228 --> 01:02.562
IT IS?

01:02.645 --> 01:04.480
I GUESS IT'S OK.

01:04.563 --> 01:06.107
{\an1}IT'S NOT LIKE YOU
TOLD HER YOU LOVED HER.

01:06.191 --> 01:06.483
{\an1}THAT WOULD REALLY
FREAK HER OUT.

01:06.566 --> 01:07.984
IT WOULD?

01:08.067 --> 01:11.571
{\an1}DUH! NOTHING RUINS
A RELATIONSHIP FASTER

01:11.654 --> 01:12.989
{\an1}THAN SAYING
"I LOVE YOU" TOO SOON.

01:13.072 --> 01:13.531
{\an1}IT'S LIKE PICKING OUT
YOUR WEDDING CAKE

01:13.615 --> 01:15.658
ON THE FIRST DATE.

01:15.742 --> 01:16.993
AND YOU WROTE
"I LOVE YOU"

01:17.076 --> 01:18.119
IN THE NOTE,
DIDN'T YOU?

01:18.203 --> 01:19.204
I HAVE TO GET
THAT NOTE BACK

01:19.287 --> 01:19.788
BEFORE SUZIE
READS IT!

01:19.871 --> 01:21.664
WHICH WILL BE
NO PROBLEM

01:21.748 --> 01:22.832
AS LONG AS THE BUS
IS ON TIME

01:22.916 --> 01:24.626
AND WE
GET THERE FIRST.

01:30.215 --> 01:32.717
I'M SO ALONE.

01:32.801 --> 01:33.968
I CAN'T GO ON.

01:34.052 --> 01:35.845
I CAN'T DRIVE
THE BUS TODAY.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.472
[CRYING]

01:39.599 --> 01:42.602
{\an8}CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION
AND NICKELODEON

01:50.443 --> 01:50.944
WHY CAN'T YOU
DRIVE THE BUS?

01:51.027 --> 01:53.029
MY GIRLFRIEND
DUMPED ME.

01:53.112 --> 01:54.364
MY LIFE IS OVER.

01:54.447 --> 01:56.866
OK, WHY ARE YOU
DRIVING THE BUS?

01:56.950 --> 01:58.159
TO MAKE EXTRA MONEY

01:58.243 --> 02:00.119
{\an1}'CAUSE I'M SAVING UP
TO BUY A CAR...

02:00.203 --> 02:02.705
{\an1}SO I CAN DRIVE AROUND
WITH MY GIRLFRIEND

02:02.789 --> 02:03.540
WHO I DON'T HAVE
ANYMORE.

02:03.623 --> 02:06.209
IT'S GONNA BE OK...

02:06.292 --> 02:07.836
EVENTUALLY.

02:07.919 --> 02:08.544
WE'LL TALK
ABOUT IT...

02:08.627 --> 02:09.878
ON THE WAY
TO SCHOOL.

02:09.963 --> 02:14.592
HERE'S ONE OF MY FAVORITE
PICTURES OF US...

02:17.679 --> 02:19.889
AND IF
SHE WERE HERE,

02:19.973 --> 02:21.349
WHAT WOULD SHE
WANT YOU TO DO?

02:21.432 --> 02:23.101
PROBABLY TO
STOP CALLING HER.

02:23.184 --> 02:25.395
NO! SHE'D WANT YOU
TO GET THESE KIDS

02:25.478 --> 02:27.564
{\an5}TO SCHOOL ON TIME,
AND BEFORE SUZIE
GETS THERE.

02:27.647 --> 02:28.731
REALLY?

02:28.815 --> 02:30.900
{\an1}YEAH. WOMEN LOVE GUYS
WHO GET KIDS

02:30.984 --> 02:32.861
TO SCHOOL ON TIME.

02:39.450 --> 02:41.244
{\an1}OH, NO!
I MISSED THE BUS!

02:41.327 --> 02:43.246
{\an1}I MEAN THE BUS
MISSED ME.

02:43.329 --> 02:44.831
{\an1}BUT I'VE NEVER
BEEN TARDY

02:44.914 --> 02:46.082
A DAY IN MY LIFE.

02:46.165 --> 02:47.750
{\an1}OH, NO. MY PERFECT
NON-TARDY RECORD

02:47.834 --> 02:49.586
IS IN JEOPARDY!

02:49.669 --> 02:51.880
I KNOW.

02:54.841 --> 02:58.386
{\an1}I'LL CATCH HIM
AT THE THIRD STOP.

03:02.265 --> 03:04.309
MOM, WE NEED
A RIDE TO SCHOOL.

03:04.392 --> 03:06.394
{\an1}Mom: OK!

03:10.857 --> 03:11.941
IF YOU'RE NOT FREAKING OUT

03:12.025 --> 03:13.109
BECAUSE YOU WROTE A LOVE NOTE
YOU DON'T WANT A GIRL TO READ,

03:13.192 --> 03:16.029
{\an1}THE BUS IS A GREAT PLACE
TO GET THINGS DONE.

03:16.112 --> 03:19.908
{\an7}BUS TIME IS GREAT
FORGOTTEN HOMEWORK TIME,

03:19.991 --> 03:21.618
{\an1}BUT NOT A GREAT TIME TO FINISH
A SOCIAL STUDIES PROJECT.

03:21.701 --> 03:24.787
[TIRES SCREECHING]

03:24.871 --> 03:27.665
{\an8}YOU CAN ALSO CATCH UP ON SLEEP,

03:27.749 --> 03:29.584
{\an8}BUT BE CAREFUL WHO YOU SIT WITH.

03:34.756 --> 03:37.008
[LAUGHING]

03:37.091 --> 03:38.801
FAYMEN'S STOP IS NEXT,

03:38.885 --> 03:39.719
SO I'M GONNA USE
THE SHIFT.

03:39.802 --> 03:42.138
{\an1}TO SAVE A SEAT
FOR SOMEONE,

03:42.221 --> 03:43.598
{\an8}USE "THE SHIFT."

03:43.681 --> 03:45.975
{\an7}SIT ON THE ISLE
WITH YOUR BACKPACK
NEXT TO THE WINDOW.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.226
{\an8}THEN WHEN THE TIME COMES,

03:47.310 --> 03:48.686
{\an7}THE BACKPACK
GOES TO THE FLOOR,

03:48.770 --> 03:51.481
{\an7}AND YOU SHIFT
TO THE WINDOW...

03:51.564 --> 03:53.858
THUS OPENING A SEAT.

03:53.942 --> 03:55.568
FOR FAYMEN!

04:01.783 --> 04:04.035
HEY, FAYMEN,
GOT A SPOT FOR YA!

04:06.371 --> 04:07.705
NAME IS
MARTIN QUERLY.

04:07.789 --> 04:09.123
WOW. THE GIRLS ARE
GONNA GOBBLE YOU UP

04:09.207 --> 04:10.291
LIKE A FRITTATA.

04:10.375 --> 04:12.919
HEY, LADIES, TAKE A GANDER
AT THIS UNDISCOVERED GEM.

04:13.002 --> 04:15.046
QUIRKY MARTIN QUERLY!

04:15.129 --> 04:16.505
YOU GOTTA HELP ME.

04:16.589 --> 04:19.216
{\an1}I GOTTA GET THIS BUS MOVING
OR NED LOSE PRETTY GIRL.

04:20.843 --> 04:23.054
{\an1}BUS STOP OVER.
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

04:25.515 --> 04:27.058
WAIT UP
OR I'M GONNA BE LATE!

04:27.141 --> 04:29.310
WAIT! NO! STOP!

04:31.270 --> 04:35.608
{\an1}WAIT! OH, I CAN'T BE
LATE FOR SCHOOL!

04:35.692 --> 04:38.319
PLEASE. I NEED A MIRACLE.

04:43.491 --> 04:43.741
HELLO, SIMON.

04:43.825 --> 04:46.035
DR. XAVIER?

04:46.119 --> 04:47.286
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

04:47.370 --> 04:48.746
I RIDE THE BIKE
TO SCHOOL EVERY DAY

04:48.830 --> 04:50.039
TO STAY
IN TOP SHAPE.

04:50.123 --> 04:53.710
{\an1}BUT WAIT. THAT'S
A BICYCLE BUILT FOR 2!

04:53.793 --> 04:54.919
YEAH, I BUY FOR ME

04:55.003 --> 04:56.713
AND HANDSOME
CLEANING MAN TO RIDE,

04:56.796 --> 04:58.756
BUT HE SAYS HE'S
ALLERGIC TO BICYCLE

04:58.840 --> 05:00.091
AND EXERCISE,
AND ME.

05:00.174 --> 05:03.011
{\an1}I NEED TO GET TO SCHOOL
IN 15 MINUTES

05:03.094 --> 05:03.636
{\an1}OR MY PERFECT
NON-TARDY RECORD

05:03.720 --> 05:04.721
IS IN JEOPARDY.

05:04.804 --> 05:08.391
HOP ON!
I GET YOU THERE!

05:08.474 --> 05:11.519
{\an1}WE RIDE ON WIND LIKE
UKRAINIAN BLISS!

05:11.602 --> 05:13.396
UH-OH.

05:14.939 --> 05:16.774
YOU'RE DOING GREAT,
MR. KWEST.

05:16.858 --> 05:19.027
WE'RE MAKING GREAT TIME.

05:27.827 --> 05:29.120
THE LIGHT'S GREEN!
LET'S GO!

05:29.203 --> 05:31.789
{\an1}I CAN'T.
MY HEART IS BROKEN.

05:31.873 --> 05:34.792
I'M TOO WEAK TO GO ON.

05:34.876 --> 05:37.211
YOU NEED ENERGY.
HERE. DRIVE.

05:37.295 --> 05:38.087
IS THAT TUNA?

05:38.171 --> 05:40.923
{\an1}THAT WAS ANNIE'S
FAVORITE SANDWICH.

05:41.007 --> 05:43.843
IT'S HAM, AND HAM
CURES BROKEN HEARTS.

05:43.926 --> 05:46.262
TOP SCIENTISTS
PROVED IT.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.764
{\an1}I'M NOT ALLOWED
TO EAT WHILE I DRIVE.

05:47.847 --> 05:49.098
BUS DRIVERS' CODE.

05:49.182 --> 05:49.724
THEN EAT FAST!

05:49.807 --> 05:51.100
EAT IT!

05:51.184 --> 05:52.810
IT DOESN'T REALLY
MATTER, YOU KNOW--

05:52.894 --> 05:54.812
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?

05:54.896 --> 05:56.481
{\an1}I KNOW. I FINISHED
MY PYRAMID.

05:56.564 --> 05:57.899
I'M TALKING ABOUT
QUERLY.

05:57.982 --> 05:59.692
HE STOLE
MY FUTURE MAN.

05:59.776 --> 06:01.319
WELL, YOU BETTER
ACT NOW.

06:01.402 --> 06:04.072
WITH THOSE LOOKS,
HE'S GONNA GO FAST.

06:04.155 --> 06:05.531
WHICH MEANS...

06:05.615 --> 06:06.783
IT'S TIME TO RETURN
HIS NOTEBOOK.

06:06.866 --> 06:07.909
{\an1}HOW DID YOU GET
HIS NOTEBOOK?

06:16.334 --> 06:18.336
BUT HEY, THAT'S JUST
YOUR CHOICE, YOU KNOW--

06:18.419 --> 06:20.129
FAYMEN. HI.

06:20.213 --> 06:22.090
{\an1}I FOUND THIS NOTEBOOK
IN YOUR LOCKER.

06:22.173 --> 06:23.841
{\an1}I MEAN THE HALLWAY
BY YOUR LOCKER.

06:23.925 --> 06:25.885
AND I THINK--
IS THIS YOURS?

06:25.968 --> 06:26.636
{\an1}BECAUSE IT HAD
YOUR NAME ON IT,

06:26.719 --> 06:28.221
{\an1}WHICH MADE ME THINK
IT WAS YOURS.

06:28.304 --> 06:29.597
{\an1}HAM DOES MAKE
EVERYTHING BETTER.

06:29.680 --> 06:31.641
HOLD ON.

06:37.396 --> 06:38.898
[TIRES SCREECHING]

06:41.567 --> 06:42.443
[CRYING]

06:44.862 --> 06:47.156
THAT WAS WEIRD.

06:47.240 --> 06:48.741
{\an5}WHAT KIND OF GIRL
THROWS YOUR NOTEBOOK
OUT THE WINDOW

06:48.825 --> 06:49.992
AND THEN RUNS AWAY?

06:50.076 --> 06:51.160
PROBABLY NOT
THE KIND OF GIRL

06:51.244 --> 06:53.663
YOU WANT TO BE WITH.

06:53.746 --> 06:55.039
WE'RE MAKING GREAT TIME.
WE'RE GONNA BE EARLY!

06:55.123 --> 06:56.624
NOTHING CAN STOP US NOW!

06:59.752 --> 07:02.338
GARAGE SALE.

07:06.843 --> 07:11.180
{\an1}♪ IT'S GONNA BE A LONG TIME
TILL WE FINALLY WORK IT OUT ♪

07:11.264 --> 07:15.685
♪ BUT IT'S GONNA BE, MY ROCKETS
WILL BE ROOTING OUT ♪

07:15.768 --> 07:19.021
{\an1}♪ OH, WON'T YOU PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE DO ♪

07:19.105 --> 07:22.316
NOW WE GET
TO SCHOOL ON TIME

07:22.400 --> 07:24.902
WITH GREAT NOVELTY
ITEMS AND FRUIT.

07:24.986 --> 07:25.653
UH, WHERE'D YOU
PARK THE BIKE?

07:25.736 --> 07:27.655
OH...

07:35.955 --> 07:38.583
EH, WE RUN FOR IT.

07:41.335 --> 07:41.878
WE'RE GONNA
BEAT SUZIE TO SCHOOL

07:41.961 --> 07:43.045
SO I CAN
PULL THE NOTE

07:43.129 --> 07:44.922
FROM HER LOCKER,
AND SHE WON'T

07:45.006 --> 07:46.424
FEAR MY LOVE.

07:46.507 --> 07:47.216
{\an1}I THREW FAYMEN'S
NOTEBOOK OUT THE WINDOW,

07:47.300 --> 07:48.384
{\an1}BUT I'M GONNA GO BACK
AND APOLOGIZE

07:48.467 --> 07:51.053
{\an1}AND THEN THROW MARTIN
OUT THE WINDOW.

07:51.137 --> 07:57.268
JENNIFER, YOU MUST REMAIN SEATED
WHILE THE BUS IS MOVING.

07:57.351 --> 07:59.187
{\an8}Ned: IF YOU NEED TO GET CLOSER
TO SOMEONE ON THE BUS,

07:59.270 --> 08:02.481
{\an7}USE ROAD BOUNCES TO DISGUISE
THE CLASSIC "SEAT HOP."

08:08.863 --> 08:11.282
WE GOT A FLAT!

08:12.992 --> 08:17.914
JENNIFER, THIS IS...
UNEXPECTED, BUT OK.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.415
{\an1}I'LL GIVE YOU
ANOTHER CHANCE.

08:19.498 --> 08:20.917
NO. NO, NO.

08:27.798 --> 08:29.717
WHO LEAVES
A BROKEN GLASS VASE

08:29.800 --> 08:31.010
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE STREET?

08:31.093 --> 08:33.179
{\an1}MY LIFE IS OVER.
I CAN'T GO ON.

08:33.261 --> 08:34.597
BEING LATE FOR SCHOOL'S
GONNA KILL YOU?

08:34.679 --> 08:36.974
{\an1}NO! I WROTE A NOTE
TO A GIRL I REALLY LIKE,

08:37.058 --> 08:37.767
AND I HAVE TO GET IT
BEFORE SHE READS IT

08:37.850 --> 08:39.936
'CAUSE I...

08:40.019 --> 08:41.354
IT'S OK.
LET IT OUT.

08:41.437 --> 08:43.731
I WROTE, "I LOVE YOU."

08:43.813 --> 08:45.524
WHAT? WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME EARLIER?

08:45.608 --> 08:47.276
THAT'S WHY MY SWEET
ANNIE LEFT ME.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.819
THAT AND BECAUSE
I PICKED OUT

08:48.903 --> 08:50.238
A WEDDING CAKE
ON OUR FIRST DATE.

08:50.321 --> 08:51.989
IT MAY BE
TOO LATE FOR ME

08:52.073 --> 08:53.407
TO FIND LOVE, NED,

08:53.491 --> 08:53.908
BUT IT'S NOT
TOO LATE TO SAVE YOU

08:53.991 --> 08:55.826
FROM LOSING LOVE.

08:55.910 --> 08:56.452
TIME FOR THE WHEELS
ON THIS BUS

08:56.535 --> 08:59.580
TO GO ROUND
AND ROUND. AAH!

09:16.472 --> 09:19.183
WE'LL NEVER MAKE IT
TO SCHOOL IN 5 MINUTES.

09:19.267 --> 09:21.602
THERE GOES
MY PERFECT RECORD.

09:24.730 --> 09:27.066
WAIT.

09:27.149 --> 09:28.067
HERE. PUT THESE ON.

09:28.150 --> 09:29.485
ISN'T THAT STEALING?

09:29.568 --> 09:31.988
IN MY COUNTRY, WE CALL
IT A [UKRAINIAN WORD].

09:32.071 --> 09:33.906
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

09:33.990 --> 09:34.782
{\an1}STEALING, BUT I'LL
BRING THEM BACK LATER.

09:34.865 --> 09:37.910
LET'S ROLL.

09:44.583 --> 09:45.668
[SCREAMING]

09:53.342 --> 09:54.760
[HONKING]

10:00.266 --> 10:01.767
WE'RE DOING GREAT,
MR. KWEST!

10:15.156 --> 10:16.699
{\an1}THANKS, MR. KWEST.
YOU ROCK!

10:16.782 --> 10:17.992
GO GET THAT NOTE.

10:22.121 --> 10:24.248
{\an1}THE BELL
IS ABOUT TO RING!

10:26.917 --> 10:28.878
HEY, COOKIE.

10:28.961 --> 10:30.546
I MADE IT ON TIME!

10:30.629 --> 10:32.840
[BANG]

10:34.383 --> 10:37.011
OH, ANNIE. WHO COULD
EVER REPLACE YOU?

10:37.094 --> 10:38.804
[SCREAMING]

10:43.225 --> 10:46.270
{\an1}HEY, YOU--YOU WANT TO
GO OUT ON A DATE SOMETIME?

10:46.354 --> 10:49.482
WE COULD PICK OUT
WEDDING CAKE.

10:49.565 --> 10:51.233
HEY, FAYMEN.

10:51.317 --> 10:52.651
{\an1}IT WAS GREAT
SITTING WITH YOU TODAY.

10:56.072 --> 10:58.157
HEY, SUZIE.

10:58.240 --> 11:01.285
GIANT LIZARD!

11:01.369 --> 11:03.204
{\an1}OH, WHOA. I MUST BE
SEEING THINGS OR SOMETHING.

11:03.287 --> 11:05.247
ARE WE STILL ON FOR LUNCH?

11:05.331 --> 11:07.166
GREAT. SEE YOU THERE.

11:13.839 --> 11:14.090
{\an1}HEY, HOW DID IT GO
WITH FAYMEN?

11:14.173 --> 11:15.508
LET'S JUST SAY

11:15.591 --> 11:19.345
HE SAW A DIFFERENT
SIDE OF ME TODAY.

11:19.428 --> 11:20.012
SO YOU GOT THE NOTE?

11:20.096 --> 11:22.807
BOOM.

11:24.350 --> 11:29.146
THIS IS HER
MATH HOMEWORK.

11:30.356 --> 11:31.982
MADE IT ON TIME

11:32.066 --> 11:32.983
AND CHECK OUT
THE NEW SHIRT.

11:33.067 --> 11:34.819
IT'S FITTING.

11:40.866 --> 11:42.952
{\an7}Ned: HAIR: IT'S NOT
A SCHOOL SUBJECT,

11:43.035 --> 11:44.954
{\an8}BUT IT'S A MAJOR SCHOOL TOPIC.

11:45.037 --> 11:48.958
{\an7}YOU HAVE YOUR GREAT HAIR
AND YOUR BIG HAIR...

11:49.041 --> 11:50.042
CUT THAT THING
ON YOUR HEAD

11:50.126 --> 11:51.877
AND MAYBE WE'LL TALK.

11:53.337 --> 11:55.714
{\an7}SOME HAVE BAD HAIRCUTS,
AND SOME JUST HAVE BAD HAIR.

12:01.637 --> 12:03.389
BUT NO MATTER
WHAT YOUR HAIR TYPE IS,

12:03.472 --> 12:05.307
AT SOME POINT YOU WILL SAY:

12:05.391 --> 12:08.727
{\an8}"I'M HAVING A BAD HAIR DAY."

12:18.988 --> 12:22.491
IF YOUR 'DO IS A TOTAL DON'T,
CHECK OUT THESE TIPS.

12:22.575 --> 12:25.494
{\an8}FOR GUYS, BALL CAPS
WILL COVER UP THE WORST HAIR.

12:25.578 --> 12:27.496
BUT MAKE SURE
YOU CAN KEEP THEM ON.

12:27.580 --> 12:30.666
{\an8}AND FOR GIRLS,
SCRUNCHIES AND HAIR CLIPS

12:30.750 --> 12:31.876
{\an8}CAN TAME THE WILDEST MANE.

12:35.754 --> 12:37.840
AND NOTHING CURES A BAD HAIR DAY
LIKE A GOOD HAIR CUT.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.887
NICE! WHERE'D
YOU GET IT?

12:42.970 --> 12:44.597
{\an1}MY MOM GAVE IT TO ME
FOR A HAIR CUT...

12:44.680 --> 12:46.932
{\an1}BUT THE HIGH SCHOOL
COSMETOLOGY CLASS

12:47.016 --> 12:48.809
{\an1}IS GIVING FREE
HAIR CUTS TODAY.

12:48.893 --> 12:50.019
I DON'T LIKE
WHERE THIS IS GOING.

12:50.102 --> 12:50.728
{\an1}SO I SNEAK
ACROSS THE STREET

12:50.811 --> 12:52.897
{\an1}DURING STUDY HALL--
SNIP, SNAP--

12:52.980 --> 12:54.774
{\an1}I LOOK GREAT,
AND I USE THIS SWEET 20

12:54.857 --> 12:58.027
TO TAKE SUZIE ON THE DATE
OF HER LIFE AFTER SCHOOL--

12:58.110 --> 12:59.570
MOVIES WITH POPCORN.

12:59.653 --> 13:03.407
HAVE YOU SEEN CRUBBS'
NEW SECURITY SYSTEM?

13:04.617 --> 13:06.702
[BEEPING]

13:12.041 --> 13:12.958
DON'T WORRY,

13:13.042 --> 13:13.792
{\an1}'CAUSE I'VE GOT
A WELL THOUGHT OUT PLAN.

13:20.674 --> 13:22.009
{\an1}GOOD PLAN.

13:22.092 --> 13:25.304
SO, NOTICE ANYTHING
NEW ABOUT ME?

13:25.387 --> 13:27.223
YOU'RE A CAT BURGLAR?

13:27.306 --> 13:29.600
WHO STOLE A MINI MUFFIN.

13:29.683 --> 13:31.810
NO. TAKE
A CLOSER LOOK.

13:35.481 --> 13:38.234
COOL! YOU'RE GETTING
A MUSTACHE.

13:38.317 --> 13:40.402
I HAVE A MUSTACHE.

13:40.486 --> 13:42.071
AND ONCE
LISA GETS A LOOK,

13:42.154 --> 13:45.574
IT'LL BE GOOD-BYE, BOYS,
AND HELLO, "THE MAN."

13:46.283 --> 13:48.994
GUYS, IT'S JUST HAIR.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.121
{\an1}LET'S NOT FREAK OUT
ABOUT IT.

13:55.626 --> 13:58.587
{\an1}FAYMEN,
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

13:58.671 --> 14:00.756
{\an1}WHAT'S UP? HOW ARE
THINGS AT POLK?

14:00.839 --> 14:01.966
I DON'T LIKE
YOUR HAIR.

14:10.224 --> 14:11.100
HEY.

14:11.183 --> 14:13.143
WHOA!

14:13.227 --> 14:14.436
WORD IN THE HALLWAY

14:14.520 --> 14:15.437
{\an4}IS YOU'RE GONNA
BUST OUT OF HERE
FOR A FREE HAIR CUT.

14:15.521 --> 14:16.522
WE WANT IN.

14:16.605 --> 14:18.440
I WANT IT OFF, MAN.
I WANT IT ALL OFF!

14:18.524 --> 14:19.817
YEAH.

14:19.900 --> 14:20.609
MEET ME AT 11
BY THE PHONE,

14:20.693 --> 14:23.445
AND MAKE SURE YOU
HAVE HALL PASSES.

14:23.529 --> 14:25.948
AND...WE NEVER HAD
THIS CONVERSATION.

14:32.204 --> 14:34.456
HEY, SIMON.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.625
UM, I THINK YOU HAVE
SOMETHING ON YOUR FACE.

14:36.709 --> 14:39.628
I KNOW. WOULD YOU
LIKE TO TOUCH IT?

14:39.712 --> 14:41.046
SURE...

14:41.672 --> 14:43.966
IS THAT
BLUEBERRY MUFFIN?

14:44.049 --> 14:46.677
OH!

15:09.825 --> 15:10.951
HEY!

15:11.035 --> 15:12.703
DO YOU HAVE
HALL PASSES?

15:17.583 --> 15:20.252
UH...YOUR NEW HAIR
IS WEIRD!

15:30.012 --> 15:30.596
WE'LL NEVER MAKE IT
OUT THAT DOOR!

15:30.679 --> 15:33.265
{\an1}WE'RE NOT
GOING OUT THAT DOOR.

15:35.476 --> 15:37.061
[GIBBERISH]

15:56.121 --> 15:57.665
{\an1}I NEED YOUR
HAIR EXPERTISE.

15:57.748 --> 15:59.416
AND WHY WOULD I
HELP YOU?

15:59.500 --> 16:01.377
BECAUSE I'LL INVITE YOU

16:01.460 --> 16:02.795
{\an1}TO MY HOUSE TO SWIM
ON SATURDAY.

16:02.878 --> 16:03.879
I DON'T LIKE TO SWIM.

16:03.962 --> 16:04.922
NED WILL BE THERE.

16:05.005 --> 16:06.965
YOU NEED CURLS NOW.

16:09.176 --> 16:11.553
{\an1}WOW. THE PRINT IN
THIS BOOK IS SO SMALL,

16:11.637 --> 16:14.223
{\an4}I THOUGHT THIS
MIGHT MAKE THINGS
EASIER TO SEE.

16:14.306 --> 16:15.974
DO YOU SEE ANYTHING?

16:18.102 --> 16:20.229
NOTHING BUY YOUR
AMAZING SMILE...

16:20.312 --> 16:22.064
WHICH IS FREAKING
ME OUT A BIT.

16:41.709 --> 16:44.795
{\an1}FREE HAIR CUTS,
HERE WE COME!

16:47.214 --> 16:48.340
NED? COCONUT HEAD?

16:48.424 --> 16:50.551
IS THAT YOU?

16:50.634 --> 16:52.219
{\an5}HE MUST TEACH
AT THE HIGH SCHOOL
IN THE MORNING.

16:52.302 --> 16:54.012
{\an1}COME ON!

16:56.056 --> 16:57.850
FORGET ME!
SAVE YOURSELF!

17:09.111 --> 17:10.612
I STILL DON'T
LIKE HAIR.

17:10.695 --> 17:12.531
{\an1}REALLY?
IT'S THAT BAD?

17:12.614 --> 17:15.659
BAD FOR ME. YES.

17:17.869 --> 17:20.204
PLAN B.
HE'S INTERNATIONAL,

17:20.289 --> 17:22.708
SO WE'LL GIVE YOU
AN INTERNATIONAL LOOK.

17:43.520 --> 17:45.814
{\an1}HOW 'BOUT NOW?
FAYMEN LIKE HAIR?

17:45.898 --> 17:48.233
SORRY. STILL
DON'T LIKE HAIR.

17:51.445 --> 17:53.322
{\an1}WHAT PLAN
ARE WE UP TO?

17:53.405 --> 17:55.949
J, WHICH STANDS FOR
JAPANESE BUBBLEGUM POP.

17:57.242 --> 17:58.494
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.

17:58.577 --> 18:05.334
[LAUGHING]

18:07.002 --> 18:10.714
HEY! WHAT'S A MIDDLE
SCHOOLER DOING HERE?

18:10.798 --> 18:13.175
UH, HAIR CUTS.
FREE. SAVE $20.

18:13.258 --> 18:15.344
GET OVER HERE.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.304
YEAH. CAME OUT GOOD.

18:20.933 --> 18:22.267
{\an1}GOOD THING
THE HAIR CUT'S FREE,

18:22.351 --> 18:26.939
{\an1}'CAUSE THE PICTURE'S
GONNA COST YOU 20 BUCKS.

18:27.022 --> 18:28.857
WHA.

18:28.941 --> 18:30.859
[LAUGHING]

18:30.943 --> 18:36.907
[BEEPING]

18:37.616 --> 18:38.909
WITH A LITTLE ACCENTING,

18:38.992 --> 18:42.871
{\an1}LET'S SEE THEM NOTICE
THE NEW ME NOW.

18:42.955 --> 18:44.790
COOK! NICE MUSTACHE.

18:44.873 --> 18:46.875
OH, YOU NOTICED?

18:46.959 --> 18:49.336
HMM, LOOK, I'M HAVING
A BAD HAIR DAY.

18:49.419 --> 18:51.296
I'VE GOT 4 CASES
OF LICE IN THERE,

18:51.380 --> 18:52.923
AND I NEED TO DISPOSE
OF THESE COMBS.

18:53.006 --> 18:54.842
NOW, GET THESE TO GORDY,

18:54.925 --> 18:56.885
AND WEAR THIS SO YOU
DON'T GET ANY NITS.

18:56.969 --> 18:59.471
{\an1}QUIET! WE'RE TAKING
A TEST IN HERE.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.473
YEAH, HE'S DOING ME
A FAVOR!

19:01.557 --> 19:03.267
{\an1}WELL, THEN HAVE HIM
DO IT QUIETLY.

19:10.691 --> 19:12.943
[PHONE RINGING]

19:13.026 --> 19:15.028
{\an1}CRUBBS, IT'S PRINCIPAL
RILEY AT THE HIGH SCHOOL.

19:15.112 --> 19:16.989
{\an1}SOMEONE SET OFF
THE ALARMS AT OUR SCHOOL,

19:17.072 --> 19:19.491
{\an1}SO BE ON THE LOOKOUT
FOR ANYTHING SUSPICIOUS.

19:19.575 --> 19:21.535
COPY THAT.

19:26.665 --> 19:29.418
HEY, WH--

19:29.501 --> 19:30.460
NED?

19:30.544 --> 19:33.088
WAIT! STOP!

19:33.172 --> 19:35.132
STOP!

19:49.479 --> 19:52.232
BUSTED!

19:52.316 --> 19:53.233
GAAH!

19:56.361 --> 19:58.447
NEXT STOP,
THE BIG HOUSE.

20:01.867 --> 20:03.535
[BELL RINGING]

20:04.912 --> 20:05.954
HEY, NED.

20:06.038 --> 20:07.080
{\an1}H--H--HEY!

20:07.164 --> 20:08.332
HEY, YOU GOT
A HAIR CUT.

20:08.415 --> 20:09.625
YEAH, A GREAT HAIR CUT.

20:09.708 --> 20:11.251
{\an1}NOTHING'S WORSE THAN
A BAD HAIR CUT. HA HA.

20:11.335 --> 20:14.087
{\an5}RIGHT. I'M REALLY
LOOKING FORWARD
TO OUR DATE.

20:14.171 --> 20:17.382
I HOPE YOU DIDN'T GO
TO TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

20:20.052 --> 20:22.804
{\an1}TROUBLE? HA HA.
NO TROUBLE AT ALL.

20:22.888 --> 20:24.723
SEE YOU LATER. HA HA.

20:26.016 --> 20:28.226
THERE SOMETHING YOU WANT
TO TELL US, NED?

20:28.310 --> 20:31.146
BECAUSE YOU LOOK
VERY GUILTY.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.940
[SIREN]

20:34.358 --> 20:35.692
WELL?

20:38.236 --> 20:38.487
NO.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.989
OH, COME ON!

20:41.073 --> 20:43.533
I HAVE TRIED EVERYTHING.

20:43.617 --> 20:46.370
JENNIFER, IS THERE
A PROBLEM HERE?

20:46.453 --> 20:47.996
{\an1}HE SAYS HE DOESN'T
LIKE MY HAIR,

20:48.080 --> 20:50.040
{\an4}BUT I HAVE TRIED
EVERY HAIRSTYLE
KNOWN TO MAN.

20:50.123 --> 20:52.209
HE HAS HAIR ISSUES.

20:52.292 --> 20:53.961
FAYMEN,
[SPEAKING SPANISH].

21:00.300 --> 21:01.927
JENNIFER,
FAYMEN WAS SAYING

21:02.010 --> 21:04.680
THAT HE DOESN'T
LIKE IT HERE.

21:04.763 --> 21:06.723
HE MISSES HIS HOME
IN BRAZIL.

21:06.807 --> 21:11.144
{\an1}OH. HE DOESN'T
LIKE HERE.

21:12.938 --> 21:14.523
I DON'T LIKE HAIR,
EITHER.

21:14.606 --> 21:17.234
RIGHT.

21:18.235 --> 21:20.988
I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'S ME, COOKIE.

21:21.071 --> 21:22.948
THE MUSTACHE IS FAKE.

21:23.031 --> 21:25.075
OH, REALLY.

21:25.158 --> 21:26.326
AAH!

21:26.410 --> 21:27.953
OH, WHAT DO
YOU KNOW. IT IS YOU.

21:28.036 --> 21:28.870
OW, OW, OW!

21:28.954 --> 21:30.872
{\an5}GOOD THING
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY
FACIAL HAIR YET.

21:30.956 --> 21:32.666
THAT WOULD HAVE HURT.

21:36.003 --> 21:37.838
[CRYING]

21:39.381 --> 21:40.132
{\an1}SO I WENT ACROSS THE STREET
TO GET A FREE HAIR CUT

21:40.215 --> 21:42.592
{\an1}SO I COULD SAVE MONEY
TO TAKE SUZIE OUT,

21:42.676 --> 21:45.470
{\an1}BUT NOW I HAVE NO MONEY,
AND I HAVE THIS.

21:45.554 --> 21:47.222
{\an1}OOH!

21:45.554 --> 21:47.222
[GIBBERISH]

21:47.305 --> 21:49.808
{\an1}SO YOU'RE GONNA
TAKE ME TO CRUBBS?

21:50.434 --> 21:54.479
{\an1}NO, WE'RE GOING
TO HELP YOU!

21:54.563 --> 21:55.147
AS MEN WITH BAD HAIR,

21:55.230 --> 21:57.816
WE HAVE TO
STICK TOGETHER.

21:57.899 --> 21:58.567
JUST PROMISE US

21:58.650 --> 22:00.068
YOU WON'T SNEAK
OUT OF SCHOOL AGAIN.

22:00.152 --> 22:02.654
{\an1}SURE, BUT WHAT CAN
YOU DO TO HELP?

22:22.716 --> 22:24.885
COMBY, COMBY,
FLIPPY, COMBY.

22:24.968 --> 22:26.053
HERE WE GO. HA.

22:26.136 --> 22:29.431
{\an1}COMB THIS OVER.
COMB IT OVER.

22:38.190 --> 22:40.650
IT LOOKS GREAT!

22:40.734 --> 22:43.487
AND WE SCRAPED
TOGETHER $17.52.

22:43.570 --> 22:47.115
SO YOU'LL HAVE TO GO
SMALL ON THE POPCORN.

22:47.199 --> 22:48.450
SMALL.

22:52.954 --> 22:53.663
NICE HAIR.

22:53.747 --> 22:55.707
YOU, TOO.

22:56.708 --> 23:00.670
I LIKE HAIR.

23:00.754 --> 23:02.380
I LIKE MUSTACHE!

23:04.299 --> 23:07.219
AND I'M READY TO GO ON
THAT DATE WITH SUZIE.

23:07.302 --> 23:08.637
HEY, NED.
I'M READY.

23:08.720 --> 23:10.472
CHANGE OF PLANS,

23:10.555 --> 23:11.139
CAUGHT SNEAKING INTO
HIGH SCHOOL

23:11.223 --> 23:14.684
BY SURVEILLANCE PHOTOS BOY.

23:14.768 --> 23:19.397
{\an1}BECAUSE NOW YOU HAVE A DATE
WITH MOI IN DETENTION.

23:20.732 --> 23:22.901
{\an1}SO CLOSE.

23:22.984 --> 23:25.153
{\an1}SUZIE!

23:25.237 --> 23:28.824
SO, YOU GUYS WANT
TO GO TO THE MOVIES?

23:28.907 --> 23:29.825
SOUNDS GOOD.

23:29.908 --> 23:31.493
ALL RIGHT.

23:31.576 --> 23:33.078
NICE MUSTACHE.

23:35.122 --> 23:38.166
NEXT STOP, THE BIG HOUSE.

23:38.250 --> 23:39.876
{\an1}NED?

23:39.960 --> 23:41.002
{\an1}OK.

23:41.086 --> 23:43.630
FIRE CRACKER
COMB OVER...

23:43.713 --> 23:46.299
{\an1}ACTION!

23:46.383 --> 23:49.970
WE'LL NEVER
MAKE IT THROUGH---

23:50.053 --> 23:51.763
I HAVE A MUSTACHE.

23:51.847 --> 23:54.432
AND ONCE SUZIE
GETS A LOOK...

23:57.769 --> 24:00.438
AH! AH!

24:03.108 --> 24:06.236
{\an1}MUST HAVE BEEN--
ALL RIGHT.

